# OPTIONAL — only needed if you want to publish a release FROM YOUR OWN MACHINE
# with `npm run publish:win`. The recommended path is GitHub Actions: just push a
# version tag (e.g. `git tag v0.1.1 && git push --tags`) and CI publishes for you
# using GitHub's built-in token — nothing to set up here.
#
# The installed app NEVER needs a token: it downloads updates from the public
# repo anonymously. A token is only required to WRITE a new release to GitHub.
#
# To publish locally instead:
#   1. Copy this file to `electron-builder.env` (gitignored — never committed).
#   2. Create a GitHub token with `public_repo` scope:
#        https://github.com/settings/tokens
#   3. Paste it below, then run `npm run publish:win`.
# electron-builder loads electron-builder.env automatically, so that's all.
GH_TOKEN=
